You can use `render` instead of `component`:

    &lt;Route path=&quot;/manager&quot; render={DataManager} /&gt;

When you use **component**, the router creates a new component on every render.

When you use **render**, the router will just re-render the component.

If you need to, i.e. for class components, you can pass a function that returns JSX:

    &lt;Route
      path=&quot;/manager&quot;
      render={(props) =&gt; &lt;DataManager {...props} /&gt;}
    /&gt;

